        <div class="res-card"><div class="res-title" style="color:#f87171">The 15/3 Payment Trick</div><div class="res-body">Pay your credit card balance 15 days before the statement closing date, then again 3 days before. Bureaus report your balance on statement close — not the due date. Pay to $0 before close and your reported utilization is 0%.</div></div>
        <div class="res-card"><div class="res-title" style="color:#f87171">Purchase an AU Tradeline</div><div class="res-body">Add yourself as an authorized user on an aged account with perfect payment history and low utilization. That account's full history appears on your report in 30–45 days. Can add 20–80 points depending on profile.</div></div>
        <div class="res-card"><div class="res-title" style="color:#f87171">CLI Without a Hard Pull</div><div class="res-body">Capital One, Discover, Amex, and Citi allow soft-pull CLI requests. A doubled credit limit cuts utilization in half instantly. Do this on every card over 6 months old.</div></div>
        <div class="res-card"><div class="res-title" style="color:#f87171">HIPAA Medical Debt Method</div><div class="res-body">When a medical provider shares your PHI with a collector without written authorization — that's often a HIPAA violation. Demand proof of written authorization. Most collectors can't produce it and will delete rather than face investigation.</div></div>
