              Monthly payment ~$879 &#8226; Total interest paid over 12 months: ~$547 &#8226; No upfront fee &#8226; <strong style="color:#34d399">Total cost: $547 for $10K for 12 months</strong><br><br>

              <strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.75)">Example D &#8212; $10,000 BofA 0% promo check for 15 months + 3% fee:</strong><br>
              Fee: $300 &#8226; Interest: $0 if paid before 15 months &#8226; <strong style="color:#34d399">Total cost: $300 for $10K for 15 months &#8212; the cheapest possible cash from credit</strong><br><br>

              The faster you repay, the cheaper standard advances become. Promo products (0% checks, Flex Cash, My Chase Loan) are always cheaper than standard cash advances. <strong style="color:#f87171">Never do a standard cash advance if a promo product is available on any of your cards.</strong>
