          <div class="res-card">
            <div class="res-title" style="color:#34d399">The Basic Float Play</div>
            <div class="res-body">Charge everyday expenses to a 0% APR purchase card. Every dollar you would have spent from your bank stays there earning interest in a high-yield savings account. <strong style="color:#fbbf24">&#9888;&#65039; HYSA rates fluctuate &#8212; they track the Federal Reserve benchmark rate and can change any month. Always check the current APY at Marcus, Ally, or SoFi before running your numbers.</strong> At 4.5&#8211;5% APY on $20,000 over 15 months you earn roughly $1,000&#8211;$1,200 &#8212; but this drops significantly if rates fall. Recalculate whenever the Fed changes rates.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="res-card">
            <div class="res-title" style="color:#34d399">Stacking Multiple 0% Cards</div>
            <div class="res-body">Apply for 2&#8211;3 cards from different issuers within the same week. Chase first, then Citi after 8 days, then Wells Fargo. Each card adds another 0% pool. With $50,000 total across 3 cards parked in a HYSA for 15 months you earn approximately $2,800 at 4.5% APY &#8212; but <strong style="color:#fbbf24">HYSA rates move with the Fed and are not guaranteed.</strong> Always verify the current rate and recalculate your expected earnings before committing.</div>
